========================================
Welcome to Freeland Graphic Tilesets 2.0
========================================
------
$Name: freeciv-freeland-2_0_0 $
------

This is release 2.0.0.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------		

1. Introduction

Freeland is an isometric Graphics Tileset for Freeciv game with high quality 
graphic, using the more complex graphics system offered by Freeciv client with more 
than thousand tile for base terrains (arctic, desert, grassland, plains, sea 
and tundra).
This tileset is distributed in three different set of tiles (3 different tarball):
- freeland-normal (normal size 64x32)
- freeland-medium (medium size 96x48)
- freeland-big (big size 128x64)

For more info see:
- NEWS file for history news.
- Freeciv forum (http://forum.freeciv.org):
	~ "Art and tilesets" --> "New GPL tilesets - Freeland" (http://forum.freeciv.org/viewtopic.php?t=1648).
	~ "General discussion" --> "Freeland - tech support" (http://forum.freeciv.org/viewtopic.php?t=1785).

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------		

2. Software requirements

Freeland 2.0.0 require a Freeciv 2.1 distribution.
- on Linux/Unix require the gtk client (cairo patch recommanded) or the sdl client.
- on Windows require the "Freeciv-2.1.x-win32-setup.exe" or "Freeciv-2.1.x-win32-sdl-setup.exe"
  distribution. The gtk version seems to crash on starting.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------		

3. Hardware requirements

I try it on a Pentium 4 1200MHz machine with 500MB of RAM and true color resolution. 
With only 256MB of RAM the big tileset seems to have trouble on display colors of 
some tile (this problem not arise with sdl client as reported on the forum by user Hima).

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------		

4. Installation

- Download tarball from Freeciv download Extras page http://www.freeciv.org/index.php/Extras
  or from ftp://ftp.freeciv.org/freeciv/contrib/tilesets/freeland/. 
- Unpack the tarball on your Freeciv 2.1.x "data" directory. The tileset is 
  selectable as any other Freeciv tileset (civclient -t set-name).
- Enjoy

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------		

5. License

Some graphics are adapted from GPL tilesets available for Freeciv (isotrident,amplio).
All other graphics/textures used in this work are created from scratch, or derived with 
image manipulation from the great GPL photo collection of Susanna Gross, available 
at http://strike.colorado.edu.

